		<h2>Our Providers</h2>

		<h3>Mel Carter, MD</h3>

    <div style="float:left;"><%= image_tag('Mel-Carter-MD-RGB.jpg', class: 'img-polaroid') %></div>

    <p>After finishing medical school, Dr. Carter moved to
Maryland to complete his internship and residency.  He started his practice of medicine in Hanford, California, but with both his family, and his wife’s family being from Utah, he soon packed up, and brought his family to Hurricane.</p>

    <p>In 1985, there was no medical clinic in Hurricane, so Dr. Carter set up, and started seeing patients that August.  Since then Hurricane Family Clinic has grown and served the communities of Eastern Washington County.</p>

    <p>“I had the chance to be a full time emergency room
    physician several years ago, but I really enjoy the life long friendships that I have developed with my patients,” said Dr. Carter.  “That is what family medicine is to me.”</p>

    <p>Dr. Carter also provides OB/GYN services.  “I am now
    delivering children of the children that I delivered when I first moved to Hurricane, and that is an honor to be a part of my patients lives in this great community.”</p>

