    <h3>Walter Ogden, MD</h3>

    <div style="float:left;"><%= image_tag('Walter-Ogden-MD-RGB.jpg', class: 'img-polaroid') %></div>

    <p>Dr. Ogden has roots in Southern Utah, that may be why he came here to retire after spending almost 35 years as a
family physician in Southern California.  Dr. Ogden and his wife reared eight children while living in California.</p>

    <p>Dr. Ogden received his medical degree at the University of Missouri in 1973.  He then moved to California for his
    internship and residency in family medicine.  “I got my love for medicine from my father, who was a general practitioner, and I enjoy treating all ages and health problems,” says Dr. Ogden.</p>

    <p>After moving to Utah to retire, Dr. Ogden decided he missed being involved in health care, and so he now practices
    medicine at the Hurricane Family Clinic, and at the Volunteer Clinic in St. George.</p>

    <p>“I am glad to be here at Hurricane Family Clinic, and I look forward to being a part of this fine clinic for years to come.”</p>

