    <h3>Philip Carter, PAC</h3>

    <div style="float:left;"><%= image_tag('Phil-Carter-RGB.jpg', class: 'img-polaroid') %></div>

    <p>Philip moved to Hurricane when he was eight years old.  He attended Hurricane High School, Dixie State College, and Souther Utah University.  Philip continued his education by graduating from Idaho State University—Pocatello as a physician assistant.</p>

    <p>He started his medical career in Beaver, Utah working in family practice clinic and the Beaver Hospital emergency room.  He then moved to Provo to work as the Wellness Director for Central Utah Clinic.  There he oversaw the wellness program for some 1,200 employees.</p>

    <p>Philip joined the Hurricane Family Clinic in August of 2012, and his practice has grown tremendously since.  “I love the Hurricane Valley.  It is my home. My wife, Natalie, and I are from here so it was a natural move to make,” said Philip.</p>

    <p>Philip and Natalie have five children, and a couple of pets.  “I am so happy to serve this community, surrounded by the family and friends I grew up with.”</p>

